English

[edit]
English Wikipedia has an article on:
BMW
Wikipedia

Etymology 1

[edit]

Borrowed from German BMW.

Proper noun

[edit]

BMW

  1. A manufacturer of motor vehicles (Bayerische Motoren-Werke (Bavarian Motor Works)).
    • 2014 February 21, Lawrence Ulrich, “Get Your $50,000 Hatchback Here”, in The New York Times‎[1], archived from the original on 22 February 2014:
      So BMW has conjured a tweener — a roomier hatchback on platform shoes, with standard all-wheel drive — to attract customers who crave the 3 Series’ performance but need more utility to close the deal.
Translations
[edit]
colloquial names and pronunciations, apart from the romanised "BMW"
  • Arabic: بِي إِم دَبُلْيُو m (bī ʔem dabulyū), بِي إِم دَابُلْيُو m (bī ʔem dābulyū)
  • Chinese:
    Cantonese: 寶馬 / 宝马 (bou2 maa5)
    Hokkien: 米奶 (zh-min-nan) (Bí-leng) (Taiwan, informal)
    Mandarin: 寶馬 / 宝马 (zh) (Bǎomǎ)
  • Dutch: BMW (nl)
  • Estonian: (slang) bemari, bemm
  • Finnish: bemari (fi), bemmi
  • French: BMW (fr)
  • Georgian: ბეემვე (beemve), ბიემდაბლიუ (biemdabliu)
  • German: BMW (de) f
  • Greek: Μπε-Εμ-Βε (Be-Em-Ve)
  • Italian: BMW m or f
  • Japanese: ビー・エム・ダブリュー (bī-emu-daburyū)
  • Korean: 베엠베 (be-em-be), 비엠더블유 (bi-em-deobeuryu)
  • Macedonian: Бе-ем-ве n (Be-em-ve)
  • Persian: بموه (bemve)
  • Russian: Бэ-Эм-Вэ́ m or f (Bɛ-Em-Vɛ́) (from German), БМВ (ru) (BMV)

Noun

[edit]

BMW (plural BMWs)

  1. A motor car manufactured by this company
  2. A motorcycle manufactured by this company
Synonyms
[edit]
  • (slang, car): beamer, beemer, bimmer

Verb

[edit]

BMW (third-person singular simple present BMWs, present participle BMWing, simple past and past participle BMWed)

  1. (slang) Initialism of bitch, moan, and whine.

Etymology 2

[edit]

Noun

[edit]

BMW (uncountable)

  1. Initialism of biodegradable municipal waste.

Anagrams

[edit]
  • BWM

Hungarian

[edit]

BMW
Wikipedia hu

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from German BMW (“Bayerische Motoren-Werke”).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): [ˈbeːjɛɱveː]
  • Rhymes: -veː

Proper noun

[edit]

BMW

  1. BMW (Bayerische Motoren-Werke (Bavarian Motor Works), a manufacturer of motor vehicles)

Noun

[edit]

BMW (plural BMW-k)

  1. BMW (a motor car manufactured by this company)
